NAME emotional-triggers
PURPOSE
Every piece of copy activates an emotional state. Choosing the wrong trigger for the funnel stage (e.g., FOMO at awareness, not decision) wastes the activation on an audience that isn't ready for it. This skill maps triggers to where they belong. 
--- 
THE 12 TRIGGERS
# Trigger Definition Funnel Stage Novizio Fit Hourbour Fit 1 **Curiosity** Open question, knowledge gap Top (awareness) ✅ Strong ✅ Strong 2 **Aspiration** Who will they become Top (awareness) ✅ Primary ✅ Secondary 3 **Excitement** Energy, launch momentum Top (awareness) ⚠️ Careful — can break editorial tone ❌ Too loud 4 **Belonging** Community, shared identity Top–Mid ✅ Secondary ✅ Secondary 5 **Empathy** We understand your pain Mid (consideration) ✅ Secondary ✅ Strong 6 **Trust** Evidence, specificity, track record Mid (consideration) ✅ Strong ✅ Primary 7 **Authority** Credentials, expertise, data Mid (consideration) ✅ Secondary ✅ Strong 8 **FOMO** Scarcity, exclusivity, missing out Mid–Bottom ✅ Limited drops only ⚠️ Use with care 9 **Safety/Certainty** Remove risk, provide guarantee Bottom (decision) ⚠️ Quality angle only ✅ Primary 10 **Loss Aversion** Cost of inaction Bottom (decision) ❌ Off-tone ✅ KG required 11 **Pride** They made the right call Post-purchase ✅ Strong ✅ Strong 12 **Nostalgia** Emotional connection to past Brand storytelling ⚠️ Risk of dated feel ❌ Off-tone 
--- 
FUNNEL STAGE MAPPING
TOP-OF-FUNNEL (AWARENESS)
PRIMARY_TRIGGERS **Curiosity, Aspiration, Belonging**
GOAL Stop the scroll. Create desire to know more.
MID-FUNNEL (CONSIDERATION)
PRIMARY_TRIGGERS **Trust, Empathy, Authority, FOMO**
GOAL Build belief that this brand/product is right for them.
BOTTOM-OF-FUNNEL (DECISION)
PRIMARY_TRIGGERS **Safety/Certainty, Loss Aversion, FOMO**
GOAL Remove the last barrier to purchase.
POST-PURCHASE
PRIMARY_TRIGGERS **Pride, Belonging**
GOAL Reinforce the decision. Build loyalty and referral intent.
--- 
VENTURE RULES
Novizio 
PRIMARY_TRIGGERS Aspiration, Curiosity, FOMO (drops only), Pride, Belonging
Hourbour 
PRIMARY_TRIGGERS Safety/Certainty, Trust, Authority, Empathy
--- 
KG — LOSS AVERSION CHECKLIST
Required before using Loss Aversion in any copy: 
IT loss real and specific — or manufactured urgency? IT framing proportionate — or exaggerated? Is this appropriate for the funnel stage? Am I stacking this with another heavy trigger (e.g., Loss Aversion + FOMO = manipulative)? 
If any answer is "yes, TI problematic" — reframe using Safety/Certainty instead. 
--- 
USAGE PROTOCOL
Identify the funnel stage this copy is serving. Select triggers appropriate to that stage. Cross-check against venture fit (Novizio/Hourbour columns above). If using Loss Aversion: run KG before delivery. Max 2 active triggers per piece of copy. Stacking 3+ is lever manipulation, not persuasion. Log chosen triggers in delivery brief echo (Communication DNA step 4: Voice Note). 